{"parse":{"title":"Air attack on the fortress of Koepenick","pageid":46988503,"revid":856129855,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Air Attack on the Fortress of Koepenick</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Galland_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Galland-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> was an incident in the <a href=\"/wiki/Defence_of_the_Reich\" title=\"Defence of the Reich\">air war over Germany</a> during <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a>. It took place in October 1943 and was a large scale example of mistaken identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Price_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Price-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#The_attack_on_Fortress_Koepenick\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The attack on Fortress Koepenick</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_attack_on_the_fortress_of_Koepenick&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Background\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>On 14 October 1943 the US <a href=\"/wiki/Eighth_Air_Force\" title=\"Eighth Air Force\">8th Air Force</a> staged an attack on the <a href=\"/wiki/Ball_bearing\" title=\"Ball bearing\">ball-bearing</a> factories at <a href=\"/wiki/Schweinfurt\" title=\"Schweinfurt\">Schweinfurt</a> in central Germany, a key industry which was seen as a bottleneck in the German industrial manufacturing system. <a href=\"/wiki/Second_Raid_on_Schweinfurt\" title=\"Second Raid on Schweinfurt\">The raid</a> had led to a vigorous response by German air defences and heavy losses amongst the bombers, but the city and the industry had been severely hit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Galland_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Galland-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Price_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Price-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_attack_on_Fortress_Koepenick\">The attack on Fortress Koepenick</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_attack_on_the_fortress_of_Koepenick&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: The attack on Fortress Koepenick\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>On 20 October, just a week later, the 8th Air Force sent 119 bombers to attack the town of <a href=\"/wiki/D%C3%BCren\" title=\"D\u00fcren\">D\u00fcren</a>, near the border city of <a href=\"/wiki/Aachen\" title=\"Aachen\">Aachen</a>. The Americans reached their target and bombed it, after which they turned for home. At this point German observers reported a large formation of aircraft heading south. Price states this was based on the noise of aircraft, though they were not seen;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Price_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Price-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Adolf_Galland\" title=\"Adolf Galland\">Adolf Galland</a> attributes this to <a href=\"/wiki/Chaff_(countermeasure)\" title=\"Chaff (countermeasure)\">chaff</a> dropped by the bombers drifting on the wind and registering on German radar. Whichever the cause, the effect was that, when it was reported to <a href=\"/wiki/Hermann_G%C3%B6ring\" title=\"Hermann G\u00f6ring\">Hermann G\u00f6ring</a>, the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Luftwaffe\" title=\"Luftwaffe\">Luftwaffe</a></i> leader, the attack on D\u00fcren was seen as a <a href=\"/wiki/Ruse_of_war\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ruse of war\">ruse</a> and another devastating attack on central Germany was assumed to be underway. The <i>Reichmarschall</i> took personal command of the air defence and ordered all available fighter aircraft to intercept. As these fighters became airborne, and were duly heard from the ground or reported by radar, the impression of a huge force of attackers heading south became more pronounced. As they were on the same course as the force that attacked Schweinfurt less than a week before, G\u00f6ring divined this was the target, vectoring his fighters to intercept there. As the phantom bombers passed over Schweinfurt without any ill effect to the city G\u00f6ring reconsidered, deciding they were heading for <a href=\"/wiki/Leuna\" title=\"Leuna\">Leuna</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/Synthetic_fuel\" title=\"Synthetic fuel\">synthetic fuel</a> refinery near <a href=\"/wiki/Leipzig\" title=\"Leipzig\">Leipzig</a> and another sensitive target. When again there was no bombing G\u00f6ring suspected an attack on the <a href=\"/wiki/Skoda_Works\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Skoda Works\">Skoda armament works</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Plze%C5%88\" title=\"Plze\u0148\">Pilsen</a> and diverted the fighters there. By this time, the fighters were running out of fuel, and, as the defence system of the time dictated, started to land at the nearest available airfield. As they did so, the attacking force began to melt away<sup id=\"cite_ref-Price_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Price-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  Galland also states the sky was clear over Pilsen, and ground observers could see there were no bombers, only German fighters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Galland_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Galland-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> With this the whole fantasm evaporated.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_attack_on_the_fortress_of_Koepenick&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>With the disappearance of the threat, G\u00f6ring freely admitted the laugh was on him, that he had sent the <i>Luftwaffe</i> on a mammoth tour of their own air space, and sent an ironic telegram to all concerned congratulating them and himself on \u201cthe successful defence of the fortress of Koepenick\u201d, a reference to <a href=\"/wiki/Wilhelm_Voigt#Captain_of_K\u00f6penick\" title=\"Wilhelm Voigt\">a notorious hoax</a> of the early 20th century. Both Price and Galland point out the difficulties of differentiating between friend and foe in a confused aerial situation; both observed that neither side managed to resolve the problem during the air war.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Galland_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Galland-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Price_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Price-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_attack_on_the_fortress_of_Koepenick&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Barking_Creek\" title=\"Battle of Barking Creek\">Battle of Barking Creek</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Air_attack_on_the_fortress_of_Koepenick&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Spelling per sources</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Galland-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Galland_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Galland_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Galland_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Galland_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Galland,_Adolf\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Galland, Adolf\">Galland, Adolf</a>&#160;: <i>The First and the Last</i> p 101(1954 reprinted ..)  <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978%2B80%2B87888%2B92%2B6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978+80+87888+92+6\">978 80 87888 92 6</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Price-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Price_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Price_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Price_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Price_3-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Price_3-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Price, Alfred&#160;: <i>Battle Over the Reich</i> pp95-6(1973) <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0%2B7110%2B0481%2B1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0+7110+0481+1\">0 7110 0481 1</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2236\nCached time: 20180914092153\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.091 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 619/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 2563/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 951/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 16/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 2399/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.007/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 786 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   62.818      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   62.818      1 -total\n 79.35%   49.846      2 Template:ISBN\n 24.05%   15.105      2 Template:Catalog_lookup_link\n 11.86%    7.450      2 Template:Error-small\n  9.44%    5.932      6 Template:Yesno-no\n  5.98%    3.758      6 Template:Yesno\n  4.44%    2.791     12 Template:Trim\n  4.15%    2.607      3 Template:Main_other\n  3.19%    2.004      2 Template:Tl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:46988503-0!canonical and timestamp 20180914092152 and revision id 856129855\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"Koepenick","*":"Aerial_operations_and_battles_of_World_War_II_involving_Germany"},{"sortkey":"Koepenick","*":"World_War_II_strategic_bombing_of_Germany"},{"sortkey":"Koepenick","*":"Combat_incidents"},{"sortkey":"Koepenick","*":"October_1943_events"},{"sortkey":"Koepenick","*":"19